"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkalx_nova_docs=globalThis.webpackChunkalx_nova_docs||[]).push([[303],{86014(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"phase3-hardening","metadata":{"permalink":"/ALX_Nova_Controller_2/blog/phase3-hardening","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-25-phase3.md","title":"Phase 1+2 Hardening: Atomic Pipeline, HAL Power Management, API Versioning","description":"ALX Nova PRs #80\u201383 land the Phase 1+2 hardening work \u2014 four releases that collectively close the most significant reliability and correctness gaps identified in the foundation analysis. Here is what changed and what it means for devices in the field.","date":"2026-03-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/ALX_Nova_Controller_2/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"hal","permalink":"/ALX_Nova_Controller_2/blog/tags/hal"},{"inline":true,"label":"audio-pipeline","permalink":"/ALX_Nova_Controller_2/blog/tags/audio-pipeline"}],"readingTime":2.73,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Schmackos","url":"https://github.com/Schmackos","imageURL":"https://github.com/Schmackos.png","key":"schmackos","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"phase3-hardening","title":"Phase 1+2 Hardening: Atomic Pipeline, HAL Power Management, API Versioning","authors":["schmackos"],"date":"2026-03-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["release","hal","audio-pipeline"]},"unlisted":false},"content":"ALX Nova PRs #80\u201383 land the Phase 1+2 hardening work \u2014 four releases that collectively close the most significant reliability and correctness gaps identified in the foundation analysis. Here is what changed and what it means for devices in the field.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## What Changed\\n\\n### PR #80 \u2014 WebSocket Protocol Version + JSON Envelope Helper\\n\\nEvery initial WebSocket broadcast now includes a `protocolVersion` field. Clients that depend on specific broadcast shapes can check this field and warn the user if the firmware is newer or older than expected.\\n\\nA new `json_response()` helper standardises the REST response envelope. All new endpoints use `{\\"ok\\": true, \\"data\\": {...}}` for success and `{\\"ok\\": false, \\"error\\": \\"...\\"}` for failure, giving API consumers a consistent shape to pattern-match against.\\n\\n### PR #81 \u2014 HAL Fault Persistence (NVS)\\n\\nHAL device faults are now persisted to NVS and survive reboots. If a device enters the Error state and the device is not physically present when the firmware restarts, the fault record is preserved and surfaced via `GET /api/hal/faults`. This makes diagnosis of intermittent hardware failures dramatically easier \u2014 the fault is no longer lost the moment the device reboots.\\n\\nFaults can be cleared explicitly via `DELETE /api/hal/faults/:slot` or `DELETE /api/hal/faults` (all faults).\\n\\n### PR #82 \u2014 Pipeline Latency Measurement\\n\\nThe audio pipeline now measures and reports end-to-end latency in microseconds. `GET /api/pipeline/status` includes a `timing` object with `totalE2eUs`, `dspUs`, and `matrixUs` fields. This gives a concrete, measurable baseline for DSP optimisation work and makes it straightforward to verify that a new DSP stage does not push latency past acceptable bounds.\\n\\n### PR #83 \u2014 Lock-Free Atomic Sink/Source Operations + HAL Power Management\\n\\n**Atomic pipeline operations:** The previous implementation used `vTaskSuspendAll()` to protect sink and source list mutations. This has been replaced with an `__ATOMIC_RELEASE` / `__ATOMIC_ACQUIRE` sentinel pattern \u2014 sink and source pointer swaps are now lock-free. `ScopedSchedulerSuspend` is removed. The audio task on Core 1 is no longer blocked during HAL init/deinit operations.\\n\\n**HAL power management:** Devices that report `HAL_CAP_POWER_MGMT` (capability bit 13) now participate in a three-state power model: `ACTIVE`, `STANDBY`, and `OFF`. Power state is controllable via `POST /api/hal/devices/power` and reflected in the WebSocket broadcast and web UI device cards. The `HalPowerState` enum is defined in `src/hal/hal_types.h`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Upgrade Instructions\\n\\nUpdate via the web dashboard: **Settings > OTA > Check for Updates**. The update applies automatically and reboots the device. No configuration changes are required after the update.\\n\\nIf you prefer manual flashing, download the `.bin` from the [GitHub Releases page](https://github.com/Schmackos/ALX_Nova_Controller_2/releases) and upload it via the Manual Upload area in the OTA panel.\\n\\n## Breaking Changes\\n\\nNone. All REST and WebSocket API changes in this release are additive \u2014 new fields are added, no existing fields are removed or renamed. Existing clients will continue to work without modification.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What Is Next\\n\\nThe roadmap for Phase 3 includes:\\n\\n- **Hardware ASRC** \u2014 polyphase sample rate conversion engine for cross-domain mixing (tracking in `feature/phase2-asrc-dsd`)\\n- **DSD passthrough** \u2014 native DSD/DoP routing through the matrix to DACs that report `HAL_CAP_DSD`\\n- **ES module build** \u2014 migrating `web_src/` to proper ES modules with a bundler step\\n- **Loadable plugins** \u2014 HAL driver loading from LittleFS at runtime, without a firmware reflash\\n\\nFollow progress on [GitHub](https://github.com/Schmackos/ALX_Nova_Controller_2)."}]}}')}}]);